{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:psalms.78",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 78,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 78 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:1",
      "text": "Hear my teaching, my people. Turn your ears to the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:2",
      "text": "I will open my mouth in a parable. I will utter dark sayings of old,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:3",
      "text": "which we have heard and known, and our fathers have told us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:4",
      "text": "We will not hide them from their children, telling to the generation to come the praises of Yahweh, his strength, and his wondrous deeds that he has done.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:5",
      "text": "For he established a covenant in Jacob, and appointed a teaching in Israel, which he commanded our fathers, that they should make them known to their children;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:6",
      "text": "that the generation to come might know, even the children who should be born; who should arise and tell their children,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:7",
      "text": "that they might set their hope in God, and not forget God’s deeds, but keep his commandments,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:8",
      "text": "and might not be as their fathers— a stubborn and rebellious generation, a generation that didn’t make their hearts loyal, whose spirit was not steadfast with God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:9",
      "text": "The children of Ephraim, being armed and carrying bows, turned back in the day of battle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:10",
      "text": "They didn’t keep God’s covenant, and refused to walk in his law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:11",
      "text": "They forgot his doings, his wondrous deeds that he had shown them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:12",
      "text": "He did marvelous things in the sight of their fathers, in the land of Egypt, in the field of Zoan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:13",
      "text": "He split the sea, and caused them to pass through. He made the waters stand as a heap.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:14",
      "text": "In the daytime he also led them with a cloud, and all night with a light of fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:15",
      "text": "He split rocks in the wilderness, and gave them drink abundantly as out of the depths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:16",
      "text": "He brought streams also out of the rock, and caused waters to run down like rivers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:17",
      "text": "Yet they still went on to sin against him, to rebel against the Most High in the desert.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:18",
      "text": "They tempted God in their heart by asking food according to their desire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:19",
      "text": "Yes, they spoke against God. They said, “Can God prepare a table in the wilderness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:20",
      "text": "Behold, he struck the rock, so that waters gushed out, and streams overflowed. Can he give bread also? Will he provide meat for his people?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:21",
      "text": "Therefore Yahweh heard, and was angry. A fire was kindled against Jacob, anger also went up against Israel,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:22",
      "text": "because they didn’t believe in God, and didn’t trust in his salvation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:23",
      "text": "Yet he commanded the skies above, and opened the doors of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:24",
      "text": "He rained down manna on them to eat, and gave them food from the sky.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:25",
      "text": "Man ate the bread of angels. He sent them food to the full.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:26",
      "text": "He caused the east wind to blow in the sky. By his power he guided the south wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:27",
      "text": "He also rained meat on them as the dust, winged birds as the sand of the seas.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:28",
      "text": "He let them fall in the middle of their camp, around their habitations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:29",
      "text": "So they ate, and were well filled. He gave them their own desire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:30",
      "text": "They didn’t turn from their cravings. Their food was yet in their mouths,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:31",
      "text": "when the anger of God went up against them, killed some of their strongest, and struck down the young men of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:32",
      "text": "For all this they still sinned, and didn’t believe in his wondrous works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:33",
      "text": "Therefore he consumed their days in vanity, and their years in terror.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:34",
      "text": "When he killed them, then they inquired after him. They returned and sought God earnestly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:35",
      "text": "They remembered that God was their rock, the Most High God, their redeemer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:36",
      "text": "But they flattered him with their mouth, and lied to him with their tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:37",
      "text": "For their heart was not right with him, neither were they faithful in his covenant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.38",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:38",
      "text": "But he, being merciful, forgave iniquity, and didn’t destroy them. Yes, many times he turned his anger away, and didn’t stir up all his wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.39",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:39",
      "text": "He remembered that they were but flesh, a wind that passes away, and doesn’t come again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.40",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:40",
      "text": "How often they rebelled against him in the wilderness, and grieved him in the desert!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.41",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:41",
      "text": "They turned again and tempted God, and provoked the Holy One of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.42",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:42",
      "text": "They didn’t remember his hand, nor the day when he redeemed them from the adversary;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.43",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:43",
      "text": "how he set his signs in Egypt, his wonders in the field of Zoan,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.44",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:44",
      "text": "he turned their rivers into blood, and their streams, so that they could not drink.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.45",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:45",
      "text": "He sent among them swarms of flies, which devoured them; and frogs, which destroyed them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.46",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:46",
      "text": "He also gave their increase to the caterpillar, and their labor to the locust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.47",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:47",
      "text": "He destroyed their vines with hail, their sycamore fig trees with frost.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.48",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:48",
      "text": "He also gave over their livestock to the hail, and their flocks to hot thunderbolts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.49",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:49",
      "text": "He threw on them the fierceness of his anger, wrath, indignation, and trouble, and a band of angels of evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.50",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:50",
      "text": "He made a path for his anger. He didn’t spare their soul from death, but gave their life over to the pestilence,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.51",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:51",
      "text": "and struck all the firstborn in Egypt, the chief of their strength in the tents of Ham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.52",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:52",
      "text": "But he led out his own people like sheep, and guided them in the wilderness like a flock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.53",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:53",
      "text": "He led them safely, so that they weren’t afraid, but the sea overwhelmed their enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.54",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:54",
      "text": "He brought them to the border of his sanctuary, to this mountain, which his right hand had taken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.55",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:55",
      "text": "He also drove out the nations before them, allotted them for an inheritance by line, and made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.56",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:56",
      "text": "Yet they tempted and rebelled against the Most High God, and didn’t keep his testimonies,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.57",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:57",
      "text": "but turned back, and dealt treacherously like their fathers. They were twisted like a deceitful bow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.58",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:58",
      "text": "For they provoked him to anger with their high places, and moved him to jealousy with their engraved images.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.59",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 59,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:59",
      "text": "When God heard this, he was angry, and greatly abhorred Israel,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.60",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 60,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:60",
      "text": "so that he abandoned the tent of Shiloh, the tent which he placed among men,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.61",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:61",
      "text": "and delivered his strength into captivity, his glory into the adversary’s hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.62",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:62",
      "text": "He also gave his people over to the sword, and was angry with his inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.63",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:63",
      "text": "Fire devoured their young men. Their virgins had no wedding song.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.64",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 64,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:64",
      "text": "Their priests fell by the sword, and their widows couldn’t weep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.65",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 65,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:65",
      "text": "Then the Lord awakened as one out of sleep, like a mighty man who shouts by reason of wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.66",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 66,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:66",
      "text": "He struck his adversaries backward. He put them to a perpetual reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.67",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 67,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:67",
      "text": "Moreover he rejected the tent of Joseph, and didn’t choose the tribe of Ephraim,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.68",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 68,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:68",
      "text": "But chose the tribe of Judah, Mount Zion which he loved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.69",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 69,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:69",
      "text": "He built his sanctuary like the heights, like the earth which he has established forever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.78.70",
      "translationId": "web",
